 16:00 UTC using a premium index methodology. The exchange's zero maker fee structure means arbitrageurs only pay taker fees when entering positions, reducing execution costs significantly. MEXC's funding rate caps at ±0.75% per cycle to prevent extreme rates, while their high leverage options up to 125x allow for capital-efficient arbitrage strategies."}]]}],"$Lf",["$L10","$L11","$L12"],"$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]]}]
